{"ts": "2026-04-04T15:00:15.151", "event": "PostToolUse:raw_input", "raw_input": {"session_id": "40302fac-b037-4b24-b2d0-deb954ba8d45", "transcript_path": "/home/emhar/.claude/projects/-home-emhar-avaris-ai/40302fac-b037-4b24-b2d0-deb954ba8d45.jsonl", "cwd": "/home/emhar/avaris-ai", "permission_mode": "plan", "hook_event_name": "PostToolUse", "tool_name": "Read", "tool_input": {"file_path": "/home/emhar/avaris-ai/.claude/hooks/workflow/guards/skill_guard.py"}, "tool_response": {"type": "text", "file": {"filePath": "/home/emhar/avaris-ai/.claude/hooks/workflow/guards/skill_guard.py", "content": "\"\"\"skill_guard.py \u2014 Intercepts /plan and /implement skill invocations.\n\nHandles PostToolUse(Skill) and UserPromptSubmit events.\nActivates workflow state with flat state model.\n\"\"\"\n\nimport sys\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nsys.path.insert(0, str(Path(__file__).resolve().parent.parent.parent))\n\nfrom workflow.config import STORY_ID_PATTERN\nfrom workflow.state_store import StateStore\n\n\ndef _parse_skill_and_args(hook_input: dict) -> tuple[str, str]:\n    \"\"\"Extract skill name and args from PostToolUse(Skill) or UserPromptSubmit.\"\"\"\n    event = hook_input.get(\"hook_event_name\", \"\")\n    if event == \"UserPromptSubmit\":\n        prompt = hook_input.get(\"prompt\", \"\").strip()\n        if not prompt.startswith(\"/\"):\n            return \"\", \"\"\n        parts = prompt[1:].split(\" \", 1)\n        skill = parts[0]\n        args = parts[1] if len(parts) > 1 else \"\"\n        return skill, args\n    elif event == \"PostToolUse\":\n        tool_input = hook_input.get(\"tool_input\", {})\n        return tool_input.get(\"skill\", \"\"), tool_input.get(\"args\", \"\")\n    return \"\", \"\"\n\n\ndef _parse_skip_args(args: str) -> dict:\n    return {\n        \"skip_explore\": \"--skip-explore\" in args or \"--skip-all\" in args,\n        \"skip_research\": \"--skip-research\" in args or \"--skip-all\" in args,\n    }\n\n\ndef _parse_instructions(args: str) -> str:\n    flags = [\"--skip-explore\", \"--skip-research\", \"--skip-all\", \"--tdd\"]\n    # Also remove story IDs\n    text = STORY_ID_PATTERN.sub(\"\", args)\n    for flag in flags:\n        text = text.replace(flag, \"\")\n    return text.strip()\n\n\ndef _parse_story_id(args: str) -> str | None:\n    m = STORY_ID_PATTERN.search(args)\n    return m.group(1) if m else None\n\n\ndef _initial_state(workflow_type: str, args: str) -> dict:\n    skip = _parse_skip_args(args)\n    instructions = _parse_instructions(args)\n    story_id = _parse_story_id(args) if workflow_type == \"implement\" else None\n    tdd = \"--tdd\" in args\n\n    # Determine starting phase\n    if skip[\"skip_explore\"] and skip[\"skip_research\"]:\n        phase = \"plan\"\n    else:\n        phase = \"explore\"\n\n    return {\n        \"workflow_active\": True,\n        \"workflow_type\": workflow_type,\n        \"phase\": phase,\n        \"tdd\": tdd,\n        \"story_id\": story_id,\n        \"skip_explore\": skip[\"skip_explore\"],\n        \"skip_research\": skip[\"skip_research\"],\n        \"instructions\": instructions,\n        \"agents\": [],\n        \"plan_file\": None,\n        \"plan_written\": False,\n        \"plan_review_iteration\": 0,\n        \"plan_review_scores\": None,\n        \"plan_review_status\": None,\n        \"tasks_created\": 0,\n        \"test_files_created\": [],\n        \"test_review_result\": None,\n        \"test_run_executed\": False,\n        \"validation_result\": None,\n        \"pr_status\": \"pending\",\n        \"ci_status\": \"pending\",\n        \"ci_check_executed\": False,\n        \"report_written\": False,\n        \"plan_files_cache\": None,\n        \"codebase_written\": False,\n    }\n\n\ndef handle(hook_input: dict, store: StateStore) -> tuple[str, str]:\n    \"\"\"Handle PostToolUse(Skill) or UserPromptSubmit to activate workflow.\"\"\"\n    skill, args = _parse_skill_and_args(hook_input)\n\n    if skill not in (\"plan\", \"implement\"):\n        return \"allow\", \"\"\n\n    initial = _initial_state(skill, args)\n    store.reinitialize(initial)\n    return \"allow\", \"\"\n", "numLines": 105, "startLine": 1, "totalLines": 105}}, "tool_use_id": "toolu_01XhsmrSmgxkz832GrDv8ctQ"}}
{"ts": "2026-04-04T15:00:15.606", "event": "PostToolUse:raw_input", "raw_input": {"session_id": "40302fac-b037-4b24-b2d0-deb954ba8d45", "transcript_path": "/home/emhar/.claude/projects/-home-emhar-avaris-ai/40302fac-b037-4b24-b2d0-deb954ba8d45.jsonl", "cwd": "/home/emhar/avaris-ai", "permission_mode": "plan", "hook_event_name": "PostToolUse", "tool_name": "Read", "tool_input": {"file_path": "/home/emhar/avaris-ai/.claude/hooks/workflow/lib/build_entry.py"}, "tool_response": {"type": "text", "file": {"filePath": "/home/emhar/avaris-ai/.claude/hooks/workflow/lib/build_entry.py", "content": "\"\"\"UserPromptSubmit handler \u2014 intercepts /build and prepares parallel implement prompts.\"\"\"\n\nimport sys\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nimport re\nimport subprocess\nimport json\n\n\nsys.path.insert(0, str(Path(__file__).resolve().parent.parent.parent))\n\nfrom workflow.hook import Hook\nfrom workflow.lib.parallel_session import parallel_sessions\nfrom workflow.state_store import StateStore\n\n\nSTATE_PATH = Path(__file__).resolve().parent.parent.parent / \"state.json\"\nstate_store = StateStore(STATE_PATH)\n\n\nclass BuildEntry:\n    def __init__(self, raw_input: dict):\n        self._raw_input = raw_input\n\n    def validate_prompt(self) -> bool:\n        return self._raw_input.get(\"prompt\", \"\").startswith(\"/build\")\n\n    @staticmethod\n    def _get_open_prs() -> list[str]:\n        \"\"\"Return list of open PR numbers by running pr_manager.py list --active.\"\"\"\n        result = subprocess.run(\n            [\"python\", \"github_project/pr_manager.py\", \"list\", \"--active\"],\n            capture_output=True,\n            text=True,\n        )\n        if result.returncode != 0 or not result.stdout.strip():\n            return []\n        return re.findall(r\"PR #(\\d+):\", result.stdout)\n\n    def activate_workflow(self) -> None:\n        state_store.update(lambda s: s.update({\"workflow_active\": True}))\n\n    @property\n    def prompts(self) -> list[str]:\n        open_prs = self._get_open_prs()\n        if open_prs:\n            return [f\"/review {pr_number}\" for pr_number in open_prs]\n\n        result = subprocess.run(\n            [\n                \"python\",\n                \"github_project/project_manager.py\",\n                \"list\",\n                \"--status\",\n                \"ready\",\n                \"-k\",\n            ],\n            capture_output=True,\n            text=True,\n        )\n        keys = result.stdout.strip()\n        if not keys:\n            return []\n        story_ids = [\n            s.strip() for s in keys.split(\",\") if not s.strip().startswith(\"T-\")\n        ]\n        return [f\"/implement {sid}\" for sid in story_ids]\n\n    @staticmethod\n    def launch_sessions(prompts: list[str]) -> None:\n        parallel_sessions(prompts)\n\n    def run(self) -> None:\n        if not self.validate_prompt():\n            return\n\n        self.activate_workflow()\n\n        prompts = self.prompts\n        if not prompts:\n            return\n        self.launch_sessions(prompts)\n        Hook.advanced_output(\n            {\"continue\": False, \"reason\": \"No further action required\"}\n        )\n\n\ndef main() -> None:\n    raw_input = Hook.read_stdin()\n    build_entry = BuildEntry(raw_input)\n    build_entry.run()\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    main()\n", "numLines": 97, "startLine": 1, "totalLines": 97}}, "tool_use_id": "toolu_01AdW3W83n7TTB6mmqNgr3Xu"}}
{"ts": "2026-04-04T15:00:54.876", "event": "PostToolUse:raw_input", "raw_input": {"session_id": "40302fac-b037-4b24-b2d0-deb954ba8d45", "transcript_path": "/home/emhar/.claude/projects/-home-emhar-avaris-ai/40302fac-b037-4b24-b2d0-deb954ba8d45.jsonl", "cwd": "/home/emhar/avaris-ai", "permission_mode": "plan", "hook_event_name": "PostToolUse", "tool_name": "Write", "tool_input": {"file_path": "/home/emhar/avaris-ai/.claude/plans/floating-herding-cascade.md", "content": "# Plan: Migrate state.json \u2192 state.jsonl (Session-Scoped State)\n\n## Context\n\nThe workflow hooks system uses a single `state.json` file shared by all Claude sessions. This means only one workflow can run at a time \u2014 if two sessions overlap, they corrupt each other's state. The fix: replace `state.json` with `state.jsonl` where each line is one session's state, keyed by `session_id` (a UUID already present in every hook's stdin input).\n\n## Approach\n\n### 1. Create `JsonlSessionStore` class\n\n**New file**: `.claude/hooks/workflow/jsonl_session_store.py`\n\nA drop-in replacement for `StateStore` that operates on a single session's line within a JSONL file. Same public API: `load()`, `save()`, `update()`, `get()`, `set()`, `reset()`, `reinitialize()`, `delete()`.\n\nImplementation:\n- Constructor: `__init__(self, jsonl_path: Path, session_id: str)`\n- Uses `FileLock` on `state.jsonl.lock` (same locking pattern as `StateStore`)\n- Every operation: acquire lock \u2192 read all lines \u2192 parse into `dict[session_id, state_dict]` \u2192 operate on target session \u2192 rewrite entire file \u2192 release lock\n- Write uses temp-file-then-rename for atomicity\n- `delete()` removes only this session's line\n- Auto-injects `session_id` into state on save/reinitialize\n\n### 2. Add auto-cleanup on session start\n\nIn `JsonlSessionStore`, add a `cleanup_inactive()` static/class method that removes lines where `workflow_active == False`. Called from `dispatchers/session_start.py` on each new session.\n\n### 3. Update `config/paths.py`\n\nAdd `DEFAULT_STATE_JSONL_PATH = WORKFLOW_ROOT / \"state.jsonl\"` alongside the existing `DEFAULT_STATE_PATH`.\n\n### 4. Update `guardrail.py` \u2014 use `JsonlSessionStore`\n\nIn `_dispatch()` (line 157):\n- Extract `session_id = hook_input.get(\"session_id\", \"default\")`\n- Replace `StateStore(state_path)` with `JsonlSessionStore(state_jsonl_path, session_id)`\n- Update `_state_path()` to return the JSONL path (respect `GUARDRAIL_STATE_PATH` env var)\n\nGuards receive `store` as parameter \u2014 **no guard changes needed** since `JsonlSessionStore` has the same API.\n\n### 5. Update `recorder.py` \u2014 use `JsonlSessionStore`\n\nSame change as guardrail in `_dispatch()` (line 466):\n- Extract `session_id` from `hook_input`\n- Replace `StateStore(state_path)` with `JsonlSessionStore(state_jsonl_path, session_id)`\n\n### 6. Update all 6 dispatchers\n\nEach dispatcher creates `StateStore(DEFAULT_STATE_PATH)` inline. Change to `JsonlSessionStore(DEFAULT_STATE_JSONL_PATH, session_id)` where `session_id = raw_input[\"session_id\"]`.\n\nFiles:\n- `dispatchers/pre_tool_use.py` \u2014 line 75\n- `dispatchers/post_tool_use.py` \u2014 inline StateStore creation\n- `dispatchers/session_start.py` \u2014 line 25 (also add cleanup call here)\n- `dispatchers/subagent_start.py` \u2014 line 20\n- `dispatchers/subagent_stop.py` \u2014 line 54\n- `dispatchers/user_prompt_submit.py` \u2014 line 48\n\n### 7. Update `session_state.py`\n\nChange `SessionState` to extend `JsonlSessionStore` instead of `StateStore`:\n```python\nclass SessionState(JsonlSessionStore):\n    def __init__(self, session_id: str):\n        super().__init__(DEFAULT_STATE_JSONL_PATH, session_id)\n```\nRemove `resolve_path()` and the `DEFAULT_STATE_PATH` fallback. `session_id` is now required.\n\n### 8. Update `auto_commit.py`\n\nThe `get_story_context()` function reads `DEFAULT_STATE_PATH` directly. Change to use `JsonlSessionStore` with the `session_id` from `raw_input`.\n\n### 9. Strip `build_entry.py` of workflow activation\n\nPer user request: remove `activate_workflow()` and the `state_store` import. The `/implement` skill (via `skill_guard.py`) already handles workflow activation with `store.reinitialize(initial)`. `BuildEntry` only needs to discover prompts and launch parallel sessions.\n\n### 10. Update `lib/workflow_initializer.py` and `lib/set_story_id.py`\n\nThese use `SessionState(session_id)` \u2014 after Step 7, they automatically use JSONL. Verify they pass `session_id` correctly.\n\n### 11. Update tests\n\n- **New**: `tests/test_jsonl_session_store.py` \u2014 test JSONL read/write/update/delete, multi-session isolation, cleanup, file locking\n- **Update**: `tests/conftest.py` \u2014 update `mock_state_store` fixture to use `JsonlSessionStore`\n- **Update**: Tests that create `StateStore(tmp)` for guardrail/recorder testing \u2192 use `JsonlSessionStore(tmp_jsonl, \"test-session\")`\n- **Keep**: `tests/test_state_store.py` \u2014 `StateStore` still exists for non-session files\n\n### 12. Remove `state.json` from workflow\n\nDelete `.claude/hooks/workflow/state.json` and `.claude/hooks/workflow/state.lock`. The new `state.jsonl` will be created on first access.\n\n## Files to Modify\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `jsonl_session_store.py` | **NEW** \u2014 core JSONL session store |\n| `config/paths.py` | Add `DEFAULT_STATE_JSONL_PATH` |\n| `session_state.py` | Extend `JsonlSessionStore` instead of `StateStore` |\n| `guardrail.py` | Use `JsonlSessionStore` in `_dispatch()` |\n| `recorder.py` | Use `JsonlSessionStore` in `_dispatch()` |\n| `dispatchers/pre_tool_use.py` | Use `JsonlSessionStore` |\n| `dispatchers/post_tool_use.py` | Use `JsonlSessionStore` |\n| `dispatchers/session_start.py` | Use `JsonlSessionStore` + cleanup |\n| `dispatchers/subagent_start.py` | Use `JsonlSessionStore` |\n| `dispatchers/subagent_stop.py` | Use `JsonlSessionStore` |\n| `dispatchers/user_prompt_submit.py` | Use `JsonlSessionStore` |\n| `auto_commit.py` | Use `JsonlSessionStore` |\n| `lib/build_entry.py` | Remove `activate_workflow()` and state import |\n| `tests/test_jsonl_session_store.py` | **NEW** \u2014 unit tests |\n| `tests/conftest.py` | Update fixtures |\n| All guard test files | Update to use JSONL store |\n\n## Files NOT modified (same API, no changes needed)\n\nAll 9 guards, `reminder.py`, `hook.py`, `logger.py`, `state_store.py`, `lib/file_manager.py`\n\n## Verification\n\n1. **Unit tests**: `pytest .claude/hooks/workflow/tests/test_jsonl_session_store.py` \u2014 multi-session isolation, concurrent access, cleanup\n2. **Integration tests**: `pytest .claude/hooks/workflow/tests/` \u2014 all existing guard/recorder/guardrail tests pass with JSONL store\n3. **Manual E2E**: Run `/implement` in one session, verify `state.jsonl` has one line. Run a second session, verify two independent lines.\n4. **Cleanup test**: Start session, complete workflow (workflow_active=false), start new session \u2192 old line removed\n"}, "tool_response": {"type": "create", "filePath": "/home/emhar/avaris-ai/.claude/plans/floating-herding-cascade.md", "content": "# Plan: Migrate state.json \u2192 state.jsonl (Session-Scoped State)\n\n## Context\n\nThe workflow hooks system uses a single `state.json` file shared by all Claude sessions. This means only one workflow can run at a time \u2014 if two sessions overlap, they corrupt each other's state. The fix: replace `state.json` with `state.jsonl` where each line is one session's state, keyed by `session_id` (a UUID already present in every hook's stdin input).\n\n## Approach\n\n### 1. Create `JsonlSessionStore` class\n\n**New file**: `.claude/hooks/workflow/jsonl_session_store.py`\n\nA drop-in replacement for `StateStore` that operates on a single session's line within a JSONL file. Same public API: `load()`, `save()`, `update()`, `get()`, `set()`, `reset()`, `reinitialize()`, `delete()`.\n\nImplementation:\n- Constructor: `__init__(self, jsonl_path: Path