### 10. Clean up", " ", "-- **New**: `tests/test_jsonl_session_store.py` \u2014 test JSONL read/write/update/delete, multi-session isolation, cleanup, file locking", "-- **Update**: `tests/conftest.py` \u2014 update `mock_state_store` fixture to use `JsonlSessionStore`", "-- **Update**: Tests that create `StateStore(tmp)` for guardrail/recorder testing \u2192 use `JsonlSessionStore(tmp_jsonl, \"test-session\")`", "-- **Keep**: `tests/test_state_store.py` \u2014 `StateStore` still exists for non-session files", "+- Delete `session_state.py` (replaced by `session_store.py`)", "+- Delete `state.json` and `state.lock`", "+- Update all imports from `session_state` \u2192 `session_store`", " ", "-### 12. Remove `state.json` from workflow", "-", "-Delete `.claude/hooks/workflow/state.json` and `.claude/hooks/workflow/state.lock`. The new `state.jsonl` will be created on first access.", "-", " ## Files to Modify", " ", " | File | Change |", " |------|--------|", "-| `jsonl_session_store.py` | **NEW** \u2014 core JSONL session store |", "+| `session_store.py` | **NEW** (replaces `session_state.py`) \u2014 JSONL session store |", "+| `session_state.py` | **DELETE** |", " | `config/paths.py` | Add `DEFAULT_STATE_JSONL_PATH` |", "-| `session_state.py` | Extend `JsonlSessionStore` instead of `StateStore` |", "-| `guardrail.py` | Use `JsonlSessionStore` in `_dispatch()` |", "-| `recorder.py` | Use `JsonlSessionStore` in `_dispatch()` |", "-| `dispatchers/pre_tool_use.py` | Use `JsonlSessionStore` |", "-| `dispatchers/post_tool_use.py` | Use `JsonlSessionStore` |", "-| `dispatchers/session_start.py` | Use `JsonlSessionStore` + cleanup |", "-| `dispatchers/subagent_start.py` | Use `JsonlSessionStore` |", "-| `dispatchers/subagent_stop.py` | Use `JsonlSessionStore` |", "-| `dispatchers/user_prompt_submit.py` | Use `JsonlSessionStore` |", "-| `auto_commit.py` | Use `JsonlSessionStore` |", "-| `lib/build_entry.py` | Remove `activate_workflow()` and state import |", "-| `tests/test_jsonl_session_store.py` | **NEW** \u2014 unit tests |", "+| `guardrail.py` | Use `SessionStore` in `_dispatch()` |", "+| `recorder.py` | Use `SessionStore` in `_dispatch()` |", "+| `dispatchers/pre_tool_use.py` | Use `SessionStore` |", "+| `dispatchers/post_tool_use.py` | Use `SessionStore` |", "+| `dispatchers/session_start.py` | Use `SessionStore` + cleanup |", "+| `dispatchers/subagent_start.py` | Use `SessionStore` |", "+| `dispatchers/subagent_stop.py` | Use `SessionStore` |", "+| `dispatchers/user_prompt_submit.py` | Use `SessionStore` |", "+| `auto_commit.py` | Use `SessionStore` |", "+| `lib/build_entry.py` | Remove workflow activation |", "+| `guards/skill_guard.py` | Update import |", " | `tests/conftest.py` | Update fixtures |", "-| All guard test files | Update to use JSONL store |", "+| `tests/test_state_store.py` | Rewrite for `SessionStore` |", "+| Guard/recorder test files | Update store creation |", " ", "-## Files NOT modified (same API, no changes needed)", "+## Files NOT modified (same API)", " ", "-All 9 guards, `reminder.py`, `hook.py`, `logger.py`, `state_store.py`, `lib/file_manager.py`", "+All 9 guards (except `skill_guard.py` import), `reminder.py`, `hook.py`, `logger.py`, `state_store.py`, `lib/file_manager.py`", " ", " ## Verification", " ", "-1. **Unit tests**: `pytest .claude/hooks/workflow/tests/test_jsonl_session_store.py` \u2014 multi-session isolation, concurrent access, cleanup", "-2. **Integration tests**: `pytest .claude/hooks/workflow/tests/` \u2014 all existing guard/recorder/guardrail tests pass with JSONL store", "-3. **Manual E2E**: Run `/implement` in one session, verify `state.jsonl` has one line. Run a second session, verify two independent lines.", "-4. **Cleanup test**: Start session, complete workflow (workflow_active=false), start new session \u2192 old line removed", "+1. `pytest .claude/hooks/workflow/tests/` \u2014 all tests pass with new JSONL store", "+2. Manual: run `/implement`, check `state.jsonl` has one line with correct session_id", "+3. Cleanup: complete workflow \u2192 new session \u2192 old inactive line removed"]}], "originalFile": "# Plan: Migrate state.json \u2192 state.jsonl (Session-Scoped State)\n\n## Context\n\nThe workflow hooks system uses a single `state.json` file shared by all Claude sessions. This means only one workflow can run at a time \u2014 if two sessions overlap, they corrupt each other's state. The fix: replace `state.json` with `state.jsonl` where each line is one session's state, keyed by `session_id` (a UUID already present in every hook's stdin input).\n\n## Approach\n\n### 1. Create `JsonlSessionStore` class\n\n**New file**: `.claude/hooks/workflow/jsonl_session_store.py`\n\nA drop-in replacement for `StateStore` that operates on a single session's line within a JSONL file. Same public API: `load()`, `save()`, `update()`, `get()`, `set()`, `reset()`, `reinitialize()`, `delete()`.\n\nImplementation:\n- Constructor: `__init__(self, jsonl_path: Path, session_id: str)`\n- Uses `FileLock` on `state.jsonl.lock` (same locking pattern as `StateStore`)\n- Every operation: acquire lock \u2192 read all lines \u2192 parse into `dict[session_id, state_dict]` \u2192 operate on target session \u2192 rewrite entire file \u2192 release lock\n- Write uses temp-file-then-rename for atomicity\n- `delete()` removes only this session's line\n- Auto-injects `session_id` into state on save/reinitialize\n\n### 2. Add auto-cleanup on session start\n\nIn `JsonlSessionStore`, add a `cleanup_inactive()` static/class method that removes lines where `workflow_active == False`. Called from `dispatchers/session_start.py` on each new session.\n\n### 3. Update `config/paths.py`\n\nAdd `DEFAULT_STATE_JSONL_PATH = WORKFLOW_ROOT / \"state.jsonl\"` alongside the existing `DEFAULT_STATE_PATH`.\n\n### 4. Update `guardrail.py` \u2014 use `JsonlSessionStore`\n\nIn `_dispatch()` (line 157):\n- Extract `session_id = hook_input.get(\"session_id\", \"default\")`\n- Replace `StateStore(state_path)` with `JsonlSessionStore(state_jsonl_path, session_id)`\n- Update `_state_path()` to return the JSONL path (respect `GUARDRAIL_STATE_PATH` env var)\n\nGuards receive `store` as parameter \u2014 **no guard changes needed** since `JsonlSessionStore` has the same API.\n\n### 5. Update `recorder.py` \u2014 use `JsonlSessionStore`\n\nSame change as guardrail in `_dispatch()` (line 466):\n- Extract `session_id` from `hook_input`\n- Replace `StateStore(state_path)` with `JsonlSessionStore(state_jsonl_path, session_id)`\n\n### 6. Update all 6 dispatchers\n\nEach dispatcher creates `StateStore(DEFAULT_STATE_PATH)` inline. Change to `JsonlSessionStore(DEFAULT_STATE_JSONL_PATH, session_id)` where `session_id = raw_input[\"session_id\"]`.\n\nFiles:\n- `dispatchers/pre_tool_use.py` \u2014 line 75\n- `dispatchers/post_tool_use.py` \u2014 inline StateStore creation\n- `dispatchers/session_start.py` \u2014 line 25 (also add cleanup call here)\n- `dispatchers/subagent_start.py` \u2014 line 20\n- `dispatchers/subagent_stop.py` \u2014 line 54\n- `dispatchers/user_prompt_submit.py` \u2014 line 48\n\n### 7. Update `session_state.py`\n\nChange `SessionState` to extend `JsonlSessionStore` instead of `StateStore`:\n```python\nclass SessionState(JsonlSessionStore):\n    def __init__(self, session_id: str):\n        super().__init__(DEFAULT_STATE_JSONL_PATH, session_id)\n```\nRemove `resolve_path()` and the `DEFAULT_STATE_PATH` fallback. `session_id` is now required.\n\n### 8. Update `auto_commit.py`\n\nThe `get_story_context()` function reads `DEFAULT_STATE_PATH` directly. Change to use `JsonlSessionStore` with the `session_id` from `raw_input`.\n\n### 9. Strip `build_entry.py` of workflow activation\n\nPer user request: remove `activate_workflow()` and the `state_store` import. The `/implement` skill (via `skill_guard.py`) already handles workflow activation with `store.reinitialize(initial)`. `BuildEntry` only needs to discover prompts and launch parallel sessions.\n\n### 10. Update `lib/workflow_initializer.py` and `lib/set_story_id.py`\n\nThese use `SessionState(session_id)` \u2014 after Step 7, they automatically use JSONL. Verify they pass `session_id` correctly.\n\n### 11. Update tests\n\n- **New**: `tests/test_jsonl_session_store.py` \u2014 test JSONL read/write/update/delete, multi-session isolation, cleanup, file locking\n- **Update**: `tests/conftest.py` \u2014 update `mock_state_store` fixture to use `JsonlSessionStore`\n- **Update**: Tests that create `StateStore(tmp)` for guardrail/recorder testing \u2192 use `JsonlSessionStore(tmp_jsonl, \"test-session\")`\n- **Keep**: `tests/test_state_store.py` \u2014 `StateStore` still exists for non-session files\n\n### 12. Remove `state.json` from workflow\n\nDelete `.claude/hooks/workflow/state.json` and `.claude/hooks/workflow/state.lock`. The new `state.jsonl` will be created on first access.\n\n## Files to Modify\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `jsonl_session_store.py` | **NEW** \u2014 core JSONL session store |\n| `config/paths.py` | Add `DEFAULT_STATE_JSONL_PATH` |\n| `session_state.py` | Extend `JsonlSessionStore` instead of `StateStore` |\n| `guardrail.py` | Use `JsonlSessionStore` in `_dispatch()` |\n| `recorder.py` | Use `JsonlSessionStore` in `_dispatch()` |\n| `dispatchers/pre_tool_use.py` | Use `JsonlSessionStore` |\n| `dispatchers/post_tool_use.py` | Use `JsonlSessionStore` |\n| `dispatchers/session_start.py` | Use `JsonlSessionStore` + cleanup |\n| `dispatchers/subagent_start.py` | Use `JsonlSessionStore` |\n| `dispatchers/subagent_stop.py` | Use `JsonlSessionStore` |\n| `dispatchers/user_prompt_submit.py` | Use `JsonlSessionStore` |\n| `auto_commit.py` | Use `JsonlSessionStore` |\n| `lib/build_entry.py` | Remove `activate_workflow()` and state import |\n| `tests/test_jsonl_session_store.py` | **NEW** \u2014 unit tests |\n| `tests/conftest.py` | Update fixtures |\n| All guard test files | Update to use JSONL store |\n\n## Files NOT modified (same API, no changes needed)\n\nAll 9 guards, `reminder.py`, `hook.py`, `logger.py`, `state_store.py`, `lib/file_manager.py`\n\n## Verification\n\n1. **Unit tests**: `pytest .claude/hooks/workflow/tests/test_jsonl_session_store.py` \u2014 multi-session isolation, concurrent access, cleanup\n2. **Integration tests**: `pytest .claude/hooks/workflow/tests/` \u2014 all existing guard/recorder/guardrail tests pass with JSONL store\n3. **Manual E2E**: Run `/implement` in one session, verify `state.jsonl` has one line. Run a second session, verify two independent lines.\n4. **Cleanup test**: Start session, complete workflow (workflow_active=false), start new session \u2192 old line removed\n"}, "tool_use_id": "toolu_017N8bwhfWxu3raZB4YdAFrV"}}
{"ts": "2026-04-04T15:06:24.865", "event": "PostToolUse:raw_input", "raw_input": {"session_id": "40302fac-b037-4b24-b2d0-deb954ba8d45", "transcript_path": "/home/emhar/.claude/projects/-home-emhar-avaris-ai/40302fac-b037-4b24-b2d0-deb954ba8d45.jsonl", "cwd": "/home/emhar/avaris-ai", "permission_mode": "plan", "hook_event_name": "PostToolUse", "tool_name": "Edit", "tool_input": {"file_path": "/home/emhar/avaris-ai/.claude/plans/floating-herding-cascade.md", "old_string": "## Context\n\nThe workflow hooks system uses a single `state.json` shared by all Claude sessions \u2014 only one workflow can run at a time. Replace with `state.jsonl` where each line is one session's state, keyed by `session_id` (UUID from hook stdin).", "new_string": "## Context\n\nThe workflow hooks system uses a single `state.json` shared by all Claude sessions. This causes two problems:\n1. **Only one workflow can run at a time** \u2014 overlapping sessions corrupt each other's state\n2. **Headless sessions (auto_commit) are blocked by guards** \u2014 the headless Claude has a different `session_id` but guards read the main session's phase from shared `state.json`, blocking reads/writes that should be allowed\n\nReplace with `state.jsonl` where each line is one session's state, keyed by `session_id` (UUID from hook stdin). Each session's guards only see their own state \u2014 headless sessions with `workflow_active=false` pass through all guards freely.", "replace_all": false}, "tool_response": {"filePath": "/home/emhar/avaris-ai/.claude/plans/floating-herding-cascade.md", "oldString": "## Context\n\nThe workflow hooks system uses a single `state.json` shared by all Claude sessions \u2014 only one workflow can run at a time. Replace with `state.jsonl` where each line is one session's state, keyed by `session_id` (UUID from hook stdin).", "newString": "## Context\n\nThe workflow hooks system uses a single `state.json` shared by all Claude sessions. This causes two problems:\n1. **Only one workflow can run at a time** \u2014 overlapping sessions corrupt each other's state\n2. **Headless sessions (auto_commit) are blocked by guards** \u2014 the headless Claude has a different `session_id` but guards read the main session's phase from shared `state.json`, blocking reads/writes that should be allowed\n\nReplace with `state.jsonl` where each line is one session's state, keyed by `session_id` (UUID from hook stdin). Each session's guards only see their own state \u2014 headless sessions with `workflow_active=false` pass through all guards freely.", "originalFile": "# Plan: Migrate state.json \u2192 state.jsonl (Session-Scoped State)\n\n## Context\n\nThe workflow hooks system uses a single `state.json` shared by all Claude sessions \u2014 only one workflow can run at a time. Replace with `state.jsonl` where each line is one session's state, keyed by `session_id` (UUID from hook stdin).\n\n## Approach\n\n### 1. Rewrite `session_state.py` \u2192 `session_store.py`\n\n**Rename + rewrite**: `.claude/hooks/workflow/session_state.py` \u2192 `session_store.py`\n\nThe current `session_state.py` is full of dead code (typed properties, setters, helpers that nothing uses). Replace it entirely with a clean `SessionStore` class that:\n\n- Backs state in a JSONL file (one JSON line per session, keyed by `session_id`)\n- Same public API as `StateStore`: `load()`, `save()`, `update()`, `get()`, `set()`, `reset()`, `reinitialize()`, `delete()`\n- Constructor: `__init__(self, session_id: str, jsonl_path: Path = DEFAULT_STATE_JSONL_PATH)`\n- Uses `FileLock` on `state.jsonl.lock` (same pattern as `StateStore`)\n- Every operation: acquire lock \u2192 read all lines \u2192 parse into `dict[session_id, state_dict]` \u2192 operate on target session \u2192 rewrite file \u2192 release lock\n- `cleanup_inactive()` class method: remove lines where `workflow_active == False`\n\n### 2. Update `config/paths.py`\n\nAdd `DEFAULT_STATE_JSONL_PATH = WORKFLOW_ROOT / \"state.jsonl\"`.\n\n### 3. Update `guardrail.py`\n\nIn `_dispatch()` (line 157):\n- Extract `session_id = hook_input.get(\"session_id\", \"default\")`\n- Replace `StateStore(state_path)` \u2192 `SessionStore(session_id)`\n- Update `_state_path()` / env var handling for JSONL path\n\n### 4. Update `recorder.py`\n\nSame as guardrail in `_dispatch()` (line 466):\n- Extract `session_id`, use `SessionStore(session_id)`\n\n### 5. Update all 6 dispatchers\n\nEach creates `StateStore(DEFAULT_STATE_PATH)` inline \u2192 `SessionStore(session_id)` where `session_id = raw_input[\"session_id\"]`.\n\n- `dispatchers/pre_tool_use.py` \u2014 line 75\n- `dispatchers/post_tool_use.py` \u2014 inline store creation\n- `dispatchers/session_start.py` \u2014 line 25 (also add `SessionStore.cleanup_inactive()` call)\n- `dispatchers/subagent_start.py` \u2014 line 20\n- `dispatchers/subagent_stop.py` \u2014 line 54\n- `dispatchers/user_prompt_submit.py` \u2014 line 48\n\n### 6. Update `auto_commit.py`\n\n`get_story_context()` reads `DEFAULT_STATE_PATH` directly \u2192 use `SessionStore(session_id)` with session_id from `raw_input`.\n\n### 7. Strip `build_entry.py` of workflow activation\n\nRemove `activate_workflow()` and the `state_store` import. The `/implement` skill (via `skill_guard.py`) handles activation. `BuildEntry` only discovers prompts and launches parallel sessions.\n\n### 8. Update `skill_guard.py` import\n\nChange `from workflow.state_store import StateStore` \u2192 `from workflow.session_store import SessionStore`. The `store` parameter it receives will already be a `SessionStore` from guardrail.\n\n### 9. Update tests\n\n- **Rewrite**: `tests/test_state_store.py` \u2192 test `SessionStore` with JSONL: multi-session isolation, concurrent access, cleanup\n- **Update**: `tests/conftest.py` \u2014 fixtures use `SessionStore`\n- **Update**: Guard/recorder test files \u2014 use `SessionStore(session_id, tmp_jsonl)` instead of `StateStore(tmp_json)`\n\n### 10. Clean up\n\n- Delete `session_state.py` (replaced by `session_store.py`)\n- Delete `state.json` and `state.lock`\n- Update all imports from `session_state` \u2192 `session_store`\n\n## Files to Modify\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `session_store.py` | **NEW** (replaces `session_state.py`) \u2014 JSONL session store |\n| `session_state.py` | **DELETE** |\n| `config/paths.py` | Add `DEFAULT_STATE_JSONL_PATH` |\n| `guardrail.py` | Use `SessionStore` in `_dispatch()` |\n| `recorder.py` | Use `SessionStore` in `_dispatch()` |\n| `dispatchers/pre_tool_use.py` | Use `SessionStore` |\n| `dispatchers/post_tool_use.py` | Use `SessionStore` |\n| `dispatchers/session_start.py` | Use `SessionStore` + cleanup |\n| `dispatchers/subagent_start.py` | Use `SessionStore` |\n| `dispatchers/subagent_stop.py` | Use `SessionStore` |\n| `dispatchers/user_prompt_submit.py` | Use `SessionStore` |\n| `auto_commit.py` | Use `SessionStore` |\n| `lib/build_entry.py` | Remove workflow activation |\n| `guards/skill_guard.py` | Update import |\n| `tests/conftest.py` | Update fixtures |\n| `tests/test_state_store.py` | Rewrite for `SessionStore` |\n| Guard/recorder test files | Update store creation |\n\n## Files NOT modified (same API)\n\nAll 9 guards (except `skill_guard.py` import), `reminder.py`, `hook.py`, `logger.py`, `state_store.py`, `lib/file_manager.py`\n\n## Verification\n\n1. `pytest .claude/hooks/workflow/tests/` \u2014 all tests pass with new JSONL store\n2. Manual: run `/implement`, check `state.jsonl` has one line with correct session_id\n3. Cleanup: complete workflow \u2192 new session \u2192 old inactive line removed\n", "structuredPatch": [{"oldStart": 2, "oldLines": 8, "newStart": 2, "newLines": 12, "lines": [" ", " ## Context", " ", "-The workflow hooks system uses a single `state.json` shared by all Claude sessions \u2014 only one workflow can run at a time. Replace with `state.jsonl` where each line is one session's state, keyed by `session_id` (UUID from hook stdin).", "+The workflow hooks system uses a single `state.json` shared by all Claude sessions. This causes two problems:", "+1. **Only one workflow can run at a time** \u2014 overlapping sessions corrupt each other's state", "+2. **Headless sessions (auto_commit) are blocked by guards** \u2014 the headless Claude has a different `session_id` but guards read the main session's phase from shared `state.json`, blocking reads/writes that should be allowed", " ", "+Replace with `state.jsonl` where each line is one session's state, keyed by `session_id` (UUID from hook stdin). Each session's guards only see their own state \u2014 headless sessions with `workflow_active=false` pass through all guards freely.", "+", " ## Approach", " ", " ### 1. Rewrite `session_state.py` \u2192 `session_store.py`"]}], "userModified": false, "replaceAll": false}, "tool_use_id": "toolu_01MAKwFb3MeFrGS2qmdBdQ4T"}}
